 "awd_abstract_narration": "\tThis project deals with two major areas of mathematical relativity\r\nwhich border on the fields of 3-manifold topology on the one hand and\r\nnumerical/experimental relativity on the other. The first research\r\ntopic treats the question of how the spatial topology of the universe\r\naffects its long-time evolution. The second topic involves the\r\ndevelopment of an efficient and accurate numerical scheme for the\r\ncomputation of gravitational waves produced by colliding black holes.\r\n\tThe importance of the first topic is that it seeks to unify the study\r\nof the evolutionary properties of the universe with various\r\ngeometrization results and conjectures from pure mathematics, thereby\r\nbroadening the scope of results in either field of study. The\r\nimportance of the second topic is that it seeks to support the\r\nexperimental search for gravitational waves by improving the\r\ntheoretical understanding of possible sources of such waves.",
